Title : Nusatsum Mountain
Text : '''Nusatsum Mountain''' (2,575 m/8,448 feet),<ref>[http://bivouac.com/MtnPg.asp?MtnId=1955 Bivouac Mountain Encyclopedia entry]</ref> is a [[mountain]] in the [[Pacific Ranges]] of the [[Coast Mountains]] of [[British Columbia]], [[Canada]], located near the [[Nusatsum River]] and south of and between the communities of [[Firvale]] and [[Hagensborg]]. The mountain is the equivalent of [[Mount Ararat]] in the traditions of the [[Nuxalk]], as the place where survivors found refuge from the [[Great Flood]].<ref>[http://apps.gov.bc.ca/pub/bcgnws/names/17869.html BC Names/GeoBC entry "Nusatsum Mountain"]</ref>

Other spellings of Nusatsum seen on older maps include "Nootsatsum", "Noosatum" and "Nutsatsum".<ref>[http://apps.gov.bc.ca/pub/bcgnws/names/17869.html BC Names/GeoBC entry "Nusatsum Mountain"]</ref>

